ons. Further, using the global flow variables,\nwe compute the Bernoulli parameter ($Be$) which remains positive all throughout\nthe disc, although flow becomes loosely unbound for higher $\\Phi_{\\rm s}$.\nFinally, we indicate the relevance of this work in the astrophysical context in\nexplaining the possibility of massloss/outflows from the unbound disc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 4 Jun 2023 20:02:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-06"}
