\\mu})=(3.48\\pm0.14_{\\rm stat.}\\pm0.10_{\\rm syst.})\\%$, three\ntimes more precise than the prior world average result. Tests of lepton flavor\nuniversality using $\\Lambda_c^+\\rightarrow \\Lambda \\ell^+\\nu_{\\ell}$ ($\\ell=e,\n\\mu$) decays are reported for the first time, based on measurements of the\ndifferential decay rates and the forward-backward asymmetries in separate\nfour-momentum transfer regions. The results are compatible with Standard Model\npredictions. Furthermore, we improve the determination of the form-factor\nparameters in $\\Lambda_c^+\\rightarrow \\Lambda \\ell^+\\nu_{\\ell}$ decays, which\nprovide stringent tests and calibration for lattice quantum chromodynamics\n(LQCD) calculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Jun 2023 06:52:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-06"}
